      "findings_details": [
        {
          "file": "plugins/rq/scripts/lib/quality-preflight.sh",
          "line": 23,
          "severity": "medium",
          "category": "correctness",
          "title": "symlink-to-file at .quality/ bypasses both guards",
          "body": "When .quality/ is a symlink pointing to a regular file (not a directory), neither the dangling-symlink branch (line 23: -L && !-e) nor the plain-file branch (line 34: -e && !-L && !-d) fires. The -L test is true so the second branch short-circuits on !-L. The function returns 0, load-config.sh runs, and mkdir -p .quality/proof fails with 'Not a directory'. The comment on line 17 says the guard fires for dangling symlinks and plain-file -- a symlink-to-file is a third crash-causing state not covered. Fix: add a third branch after line 33: if [ -L \"$q\" ] && [ -e \"$q\" ] && [ ! -d \"$q\" ]; then emit diagnostic and return 1.",
          "confidence": "high"
        },
        {
          "file": "plugins/rq/scripts/gate-prerun-check.sh",
          "line": 34,
          "severity": "medium",
          "category": "correctness",
          "title": "symlink-to-file at .quality/ bypasses both guards (same gap as quality-preflight.sh)",
          "body": "Lines 18-29 and 34-43 check for (a) dangling symlink and (b) non-symlink non-directory. A symlink pointing to a regular file (-L=true, -e=true, -d=false) passes both checks silently, gate exits 0, then load-config.sh runs and mkdir -p .quality/proof fails with 'Not a directory'. The gate comment says it catches 'dangling .quality/ symlink' -- the symlink-to-file case is a structurally identical crash path not covered. Fix: add a guard between lines 43 and 44: if [ -L \"$QUALITY_PATH\" ] && [ -e \"$QUALITY_PATH\" ] && [ ! -d \"$QUALITY_PATH\" ]; then emit 'symlink to non-directory' diagnostic and exit 1. Mirror the fix in quality-preflight.sh.",
          "confidence": "high"
        }
      ]
    },
